localization.BriefingTutorial01Movements: Learn movement essentials, how to keep your engineer alive with life support energy and oxygen and how to use each of the character tools, the welder, grinder and hand drill.
localization.BriefingTutorial02Inventory: An introduction to player and cargo inventories, how to add/withdraw items and a basic initiation to control panels and terminals for controlling block functions.
localization.BriefingTutorial03Energy:
Learn how to recharge your suit energy by tackling a series of small challenges that 
  explain the behaviour of power within Space Engineers and the different ways you can provide it.
localization.BriefingTutorial04Oxygen: This tutorial covers the various oxygen related blocks, oxygen farms, generators, vents, bottles, tanks and ice, including their control panel functions. The concept of creating an airtight room for pressurization is also addressed.
localization.BriefingTutorial05OreRefining: The basics of infrastructure and industry are taught in this tutorial. You will learn how to mine ores, process them in a refinery and then commission new block components to be made in the assembler from the refined elements.
localization.BriefingTutorial06Conveyors: Setting up a good conveyor system is very useful and can save you a lot of time. Learn how to move items through conveyors and the different ways to have separate systems interact or connect with each other.
localization.BriefingTutorial07Jetpack: The jetpack tutorial displays the controls needed for flight which is followed by a series of assault course style sections to challenge your ability to fly quickly and accurately, you have a limited time from the moment you begin each section to reach the exit door. Watch out for hazards!
localization.BriefingTutorial08YourFirstShip: The true test of any engineer is the ability to build a space-worthy ship from scratch, this tutorial will provide instruction on how to build a simple one-person transport vessel. Learn how to place blocks, weld them to completion and make a simple flight, you will also be taught essential rules of ship building that you can apply to create your own designs.
localization.BriefingTutorial09ShipFlight: This tutorial offers instruction on how to fly a ship and use the three ship tools. You must use each ship in turn to navigate through several chambers that demonstrate how to grind, weld and drill as well as how to stock a weld ships cargo and how to dock with connectors.
localization.BriefingTutorial10Grids: This tutorial aims to illuminate the nature of small, large and station grids, the rules that govern them and how you can join them with the merge block. There is also a brief section on floating objects.

localization.Description_Welder: A tool for building and repairing. Hold {CONTROL:ABASE:PRIMARY_TOOL_ACTION} to weld. Press {CONTROL:ABASE:SECONDARY_TOOL_ACTION} to put missing components to Build Planner.
localization.Description_AngleGrinder: A tool for deconstructing and salvaging. Hold {CONTROL:ABASE:PRIMARY_TOOL_ACTION} to grind.
localization.Description_HandDrill: A tool to break down rock to collect minerals. Hold down {CONTROL:ABASE:PRIMARY_TOOL_ACTION} to drill. Hold {CONTROL:ABASE:SECONDARY_TOOL_ACTION} to quickly dig tunnels.
localization.Description_Rifle: The MR-20 is a staple of both military and police forces. An exceptionally reliable rifle. Easy to use, easy to clean.
localization.Description_LightArmor: Basic armor to give structure and shape to ships and stations. Not very durable but lightweight.
localization.Description_HeavyArmor: Heavy armor to give structure and shape to ships and stations. Durable but heavy.
localization.Description_AdvancedRotor: Advanced rotors enable connected grids to rotate with the ability to transfer items between the grids.
localization.Description_AdvancedRotorPart: The top part of an advanced rotor can be reattached to the rotor by accessing rotor settings.
localization.Description_AirVent:
The Airvent can fill a sealed room with oxygen or extract oxygen from the atmosphere.

Oxygen is produced from ice in a O2/H2 generator or by oxygen farms. 
Use an oxygen tank for storage and conveyors to connect the blocks.
localization.Description_RadioAntenna:
Antennas can be used to broadcast positions, messages HUD markers and allows grids to be accessed or controlled from a distance.

Antennas need to be able to send and receive, so make sure two antennas always overlap each other's position.
localization.Description_VirtualMass: Artificial mass or spaceballs enable grids to react to artificial gravity.
localization.Description_Assembler:
Assemblers are highly advanced machines capable of producing tools and components.

Requires ingots and power to produce components.
localization.Description_AssemblerBasic:
A basic assembler to produce a limited selection of components. 

Requires ingots and power to produce components.
localization.Description_AtmosphericThrust: Atmospheric thrusters can only function in planetary atmospheres.
localization.Description_Battery: A battery stores power and is able to distribute a high output of energy.
localization.Description_Beacon: A beacon is used to broadcast its position.
localization.Description_ButtonPanel:
Button panels enable you to bind block functions to buttons that can be directly interacted with.

When highlighted, press {CONTROL:TERMINAL} to configure the buttons and {CONTROL:USE} to activate them.
localization.Description_Camera:
The camera allows you to view remote locations and zoom in on distant objects.

Set up cameras on ship toolbars so you can zoom while using weapons or look behind you while docking.
localization.Description_SmallCargoContainer: Small containers can be used to store items.
localization.Description_MediumCargoContainer: Medium containers can be used to store items.
localization.Description_LargeCargoContainer: Large containers can be used to store many items.
localization.Description_SteelCatwalk: Catwalks can be used to build walkways or function as thin walls.
localization.Description_Cockpit:
Cockpits are used to control your ship.

Connect a cockpit with oxygen tanks and O2/H2 generators to supply the cockpit with oxygen.
localization.Description_FighterCockpit:
Fighter cockpits are used to control ships and offer a little more protection than normal cockpits.

Connect the cockpit with Oxygen tanks and O2/H2 generators to supply the cockpit with oxygen.
localization.Description_Collector: Collectors collects items when they get close to the collector's funnel.
localization.Description_Connector:
The connector can be magnetically locked with other connectors to allow cross grid distribution of items and power.

Toggle the magnetic lock from your toolbar or press {CONTROL:LANDING_GEAR}. Connectors will show up yellow when in range.  Unlocking it will briefly disable the magnetic function.
localization.Description_ControlPanel:
Control panels are simple panels that allow access to grid menus.

When highlighted, press {CONTROL:TERMINAL} to interact with the panel.
localization.Description_ControlStation: Control stations are used to control a large ship.
localization.Descripton_ConveyorJunction: Use conveyor tubes and junctions to connect inventories of blocks so that items and gases can move freely from one inventory to another.
localization.Description_ConveyorSorter:
Conveyor sorters can be configured to only pass specific items through or stop specific items from passing through.

Sorters can be used to filter out unwanted materials or to collect specific items in a container.
localization.Description_ConveyorTube: Use conveyor tubes and junctions to connect inventories of blocks so that items can move freely from one inventory to another.
localization.Description_CornerLight: Lights are used to illuminate interiors or can be used to act as reference points on exteriors.
localization.Description_CryoChamber:
Cryo rooms can store players while they are disconnected from a server.

Reduced oxygen consumption for player. Stores toolbar while offline. Connect the cryo room with Oxygen tanks, O2/H2 generators or oxygen farms with conveyors to supply oxygen.
localization.Description_Decoy: Decoys attract fire from enemy turrets and protect your property from lightning strikes.
localization.Description_Door: Doors can seal off interiors and make them air tight while still allowing access for the player.
localization.Description_Drill:
Ship drills are utility tools for mining on planets or asteroids to collect raw ores.

Can be used from a cockpit or turned on manually. Be careful not to get too close while it's active. Use conveyors to connect the drill with more storage blocks or refineries.
localization.Description_Ejector:
The ejector allows small items to be ejected from small ships. Can also be used to access inventories.

You can use the ejector together with the conveyor sorter to collect and throw out specific items.
localization.Description_EventController: Event Controllers trigger actions based on block or grid conditions.
localization.Description_FlightSeat: Flight seats are used to control a large ship and access all of its functions.
localization.Description_FullCoverWall: Armored walls provide cover in interiors or can be used to prevent players from walking off ledges.
localization.Description_GatlingGun:
Fast-shooting gun that can be loaded through conveyors. Uses Gatling Ammo Boxes.

Maximum range: 800 m
localization.Description_GatlingTurret:
Fast-shooting turret that can be loaded through conveyors. Uses Gatling Ammo Boxes.

Maximum range: 800 m
localization.Description_GravityGenerator: Gravity generators create configurable artificial gravity fields that affect players and items in an otherwise zero G environment. Has diminishing effects when inside a real gravity field.
localization.Description_GravityGeneratorSphere: Spherical gravity generators create a configurable artificial spherical gravity field that affects players and items in an otherwise zero G environment. Has diminishing effects when inside a real gravity field.
localization.Description_ShipGrinder: Ship grinders are utility tools for deconstructing grids. Can be used from a cockpit or turned on manually. Be careful not to get too close while it's active.
localization.Description_Gyroscope:
Gyroscopes allow ships to orientate using the mouse movements and stabilize rotating grids.

Build more gyroscopes to increase sensitivity and the speed that a grid can turn.
localization.Description_HangarDoor:
Hangar doors can be linked together to create large gates that can seal spaces air tight while allowing vehicles in and out. 

You can build and use a button panel to open hangar doors by interacting with it or sensors to make them open and close automatically.
localization.Description_HydrogenTank:
Hydrogen tanks are used for storing hydrogen fuel.

Hydrogen is used for hydrogen thrusters, engines or jetpack fuel. Hydrogen can be produced from ice in a O2/H2 generator. Can store and refill hydrogen bottles.
localization.Description_HydrogenThrust:
Hydrogen thrusters are powerful thrusters that consume hydrogen and function in every environment.

Hydrogen can be produced from ice in a O2/H2 generator. Use a hydrogen tank for storage. Use Conveyors to transport the hydrogen.
localization.Description_InteriorLight: Lights are used to illuminate interiors or can be used to act as reference points on exteriors.
localization.Description_InteriorPillar: Pillars and columns can be used to reinforce structures or as decoration.
localization.Description_InteriorTurret:
Autonomous anti-personnel turret. Must be manually loaded with MR-50A Rifle Magazines.

Maximum range: 800 m
localization.Description_InteriorWall: Interior walls are blocks with emissive lights to function as interior walls, ceilings or floors.
localization.Description_IonThrust: Ion thrusters are advanced thrusters that function best in zero gravity environments.
localization.Description_JumpDrive:
Jump drives allow ships to teleport over large distances.

They require a full charge to jump and can only be activated from the toolbar of a cockpit.
localization.Description_TextPanel: LCD panels display pictograms or customized text.
localization.Description_LandingGear:
Landing gears and Magnetic Plates are capable of magnetically locking to any surface.

They can be locked and unlocked by pressing {CONTROL:SPACESHIP:LANDING_GEAR} when inside a cockpit. They will show up yellow when in range of a surface that they can lock onto.
localization.Description_LaserAntenna:
Laser antennas do not broadcast a signal that other players can see but instead require direct line of sight to function.

This antenna is connected by using GPS coordinates.
localization.Description_MedicalRoom: The Medical room enables you to respawn, change your appearance and recharge your health and energy much faster than the survival kit.
localization.Description_MergeBlock:
Merge blocks can be used to permanently or temporarily connect two grids together and function as one grid.

Merge blocks will show up yellow when in range of another merge block.
localization.Description_MissileTurret:
Slow-shooting, explosive damage dealing, rocket launcher that can be loaded through conveyors. Uses Rockets.

Maximum range: 800 m
localization.Description_ProductivityModule: Speed modules increase the production speed of refineries or assemblers when connected.
localization.Description_EffectivenessModule: Yield modules increase production yield of refineries when connected.
localization.Description_PowerEfficiencyModule: Power modules decrease power consumption of refineries or assemblers when connected.
localization.Description_OreDetector: Ore detectors detect ores within a limited radius and makes them show up on your HUD.
localization.Description_OxygenFarm:
Hydroponics farms produce small amounts of oxygen when in contact with sunlight.

Use an oxygen tank to store oxygen.
localization.Description_OxygenGenerator:
O2/H2 generators produce oxygen and hydrogen from ice.

Use oxygen and hydrogen tanks for storage. Will refill bottles automatically.
localization.Description_OxygenTank:
Oxygen tank store oxygen.

Able to store and refill oxygen bottles. Use O2/H2 generator to produce oxygen.
localization.Description_ParachuteHatch:
Parachute hatches deploy parachutes to slow down the descent of ships when inside the atmosphere.

Can be configured to open automatically or used manually from the toolbar or settings.
localization.Description_Passage: Passages allow passage either vertically or horizontally.
localization.Description_PassengerSeat: A passenger seat can be used to transport other players.
localization.Description_Piston: The piston is an expandable block that allows the transfer of power and items.
localization.Description_PistonTop: This piston part is the top section of the piston. It has no function of its own, but can be used decoratively.
localization.Description_ProgrammableBlock:
A Programmable Block is a computer that runs scripts to manage ship systems.

Scripts can be found on the Workshop or written manually.
localization.Description_Projector:
The projector block projects saved blueprints of ships so that they can be built easily.

Projection requires a connection with a grid from a projector in order to start construction.
localization.Description_Ramp: The ramp block can be used to traverse heights or simply used for aesthetics.
localization.Description_Reactor:
Reactors generate high amounts of power at the cost of refined uranium ingots.
Uranium is one of the rarest elements and cannot be found on planets. Uranium can be found in asteroids, and in some craters left by meteorite impacts.
localization.Description_Refinery:
Advanced refineries refine all ores into ingots.

They can be upgraded with upgrade modules.
localization.Description_RefineryBasic: Basic refineries refines limited types of ores into ingots.
localization.Description_RocketLauncherReload:
An advanced version of the rocket launcher, capable of using the conveyor system to automatically reload. Uses Rockets.

Maximum range: 800 m
localization.Description_RemoteControl: Remote controls allow ships to be controlled from a distance when combined with an antenna or commands ships to fly automatically to waypoints.
localization.Description_RocketLauncher:
Slow-shooting, explosive damage dealing, rocket launcher that must be loaded manually. Uses Rockets.

Maximum range: 800 m
localization.Description_Rotor: Rotors allows connected grids to rotate.
localization.Description_RotorPart:
The rotor part is the top section of the rotor.

It can be reattached with a rotor within rotor settings.
localization.Description_Sensor: Sensors can be set up to activate ship systems when they detects players, ships or asteroids within a limited range.
localization.Description_SolarPanel:
Solar panels generate power when exposed to sunlight.

Point solar panels directly at the sun to improve the amount of power generated.
localization.Description_Sound: Sound blocks emit sounds when activated.
localization.Description_SpaceBall: A spherical block that reacts to gravity.
localization.Description_ReflectorLight: Spotlights are powerful lights used to illuminate dark areas.
localization.Description_Stairs: Stairs can be used to traverse heights.
localization.Description_Timer:
Timer blocks can be used to activate configured ship systems after a set amount of time.

Use multiple timer blocks to build sequences. Can be used to automate systems.
localization.Description_Warhead:
Warheads are powerful explosives that can be used to destroy asteroids, enemy ships and stations.

Safe when unarmed. They can be detonated manually, by taking damage or set to detonate after a configurable amount of time.
localization.Description_ShipWelder:
A Ship welder is a utility tool that can construct blueprints and blocks using components from its inventory.

Can be used from a cockpit or turned on manually. Be careful not to get too close while it's active. 
Press RMB to put missing components to Build Planner.
localization.Description_Wheel: Wheels can be used to traverse terrain in environments with gravity.
localization.Description_Suspension: Suspensions are highly durable and enable vehicles to drive over most terrains.
localization.Description_Window: Transparent windows will keep the air in and space out while you enjoy the view.
localization.Description_VerticalWindow: Vertical windows can be used to funnel air through and keep engineers out.
localization.Description_DiagonalWindow: Diagonal window shutters can be used as stairs.
localization.Description_SurvivalKit: All in one factory to get a space engineer started, but it has limited refining and assembling capabilities. Allows the player to recharge.
localization.Description_WindTurbine: The Wind turbine generates low amounts of power when exposed to open areas. Only works on planets with atmosphere.
localization.Description_PowerGenerator: The hydrogen engine converts hydrogen into power and has its own internal hydrogen tank.
localization.Description_Ladder: The ladder enables you to traverse vertical spaces.
localization.Description_Desk: A desk for decorating interiors. Can be used as a seat.
localization.Description_DeskCorner: A desk for decorating interiors. Can be used as a seat.
localization.Description_FoodDispenser: A vending machine used to distract engineers from the hazards of space and boost morale.
localization.Description_Jukebox: A device that plays music. Great for hosting dance parties or winding down after a hard day’s work.
localization.Description_OpenCockpitLarge: Seat in between lots of consoles. More like a bridge seat.
localization.Description_OpenCockpitSmall: This control seat can be used to pilot anything from modest rovers to small-scale ships; they're also exceptionally comfortable.
localization.Description_LabEquipment: Whether you’re conducting experiments or you simply want to look smart, lab equipment is perfect for decorating interiors.
localization.Description_Shower: A shower for decorating interiors and an ideal place to practice singing. Show everyone you care about hygiene.
localization.Description_WindowWall: Transparent windows will keep the air inside and space outside while you enjoy the view in style.
localization.Description_WindowWallLeft: Transparent windows will keep the air inside and space outside while you enjoy the view in style.
localization.Description_WindowWallRight: Transparent windows will keep the air inside and space outside while you enjoy the view in style.
localization.Description_MedicalStation: A decorative station that allows engineers to examine their injuries.
localization.Description_TransparentLCD: Transparent LCD panels display pictograms, scripts or customized text.
localization.Description_RailingStraight: Railings stop engineers from falling off dangerous ledges. Safety first!
localization.Description_RailingDouble: Railings stop engineers from falling off dangerous ledges. Safety first!
localization.Description_RailingCorner: Railings stop engineers from falling off dangerous ledges. Safety first!
localization.Description_RailingDiagonal: Railings stop engineers from falling off dangerous ledges. Safety first!
localization.Description_GratedCatwalk: Catwalks can be used to create safe walkways throughout your creations.
localization.Description_GratedCatwalkCorner: Catwalks can be used to create safe walkways throughout your creations.
localization.Description_GratedCatwalkStraight: Catwalks can be used to create safe walkways throughout your creations.
localization.Description_GratedCatwalkWall: Catwalks can be used to create safe walkways throughout your creations.
localization.Description_GratedStairs: Stairs can be used to create safe walkways throughout your creations.
localization.Description_GratedHalfStairs: Stairs can be used to create safe walkways throughout your creations.
localization.Description_RotatingLight: A rotating light to alert engineers of hazardous situations.
localization.Description_Freight: Crates left scattered around, indicating hard working engineers have been working in the area.
localization.Description_Lockers: Personalized lockers for decorating interiors and store your essentials.
localization.Description_LockerRoom: A locker to store tools, weapons, ammunition and bottles.
localization.Description_LockerRoomCorner: A locker to store tools, weapons, ammunition and bottles.
localization.Description_Couch: A couch for decorating interiors. Can be used as a seat.
localization.Description_CornerCouch: A couch for decorating interior corners. Can be used as a seat.
localization.Description_Bathroom: A toilet for decorating interiors. Can be used as a seat.
localization.Description_BathroomOpen: A toilet for decorating interiors. Can be used as a seat.
localization.Description_ToiletSeat: A toilet for decorating interiors. Can be used as a seat.
localization.Description_Console: A console table for decorating interiors, projecting ships and stations in custom scale, as well as displaying pictograms or customized text on its displays.
localization.Description_CockpitIndustrial:
Cockpits are used to control your ship.

Connect a cockpit with oxygen tanks and O2/H2 generators to supply the cockpit with oxygen.
localization.Description_Bed: A bed for decorating interiors. Can preserve the players' inventory and toolbar while they're offline and keeps them alive as long as there is oxygen available in environment.

localization.Quote00Text: Scientists discover the world that exists; Engineers create the world that never was.
localization.Quote01Text: Scientific discovery and scientific knowledge have been achieved only by those who have gone in pursuit of it without any practical purpose whatsoever in view.
localization.Quote02Text: Give me a lever long enough and a fulcrum on which to place it, and I shall move the world.
localization.Quote03Text: When a distinguished but elderly scientist states that something is possible, he is almost certainly right. When he states that something is impossible, he is very probably wrong.
localization.Quote04Text: Science may set limits to knowledge, but should not set limits to imagination.
localization.Quote05Text: Nothing shocks me. I'm a scientist.
localization.Quote06Text: Science is organized knowledge. Wisdom is organized life.
localization.Quote07Text: A new scientific truth does not triumph by convincing its opponents and making them see the light, but rather because its opponents eventually die, and a new generation grows up that is familiar with it.
localization.Quote08Text: An investment in knowledge pays the best interest.
localization.Quote09Text: Anyone who has never made a mistake has never tried anything new.
localization.Quote10Text: Nature never breaks her own laws.
localization.Quote12Text: Where there is shouting, there is no true knowledge.
localization.Quote13Text: I have offended God and mankind because my work didn't reach the quality it should have.
localization.Quote14Text: All our knowledge has its origins in our perceptions.
localization.Quote15Text: By denying scientific principles, one may maintain any paradox.
localization.Quote16Text: Mathematics is the language in which God has written the universe.
localization.Quote17Text: If I were again beginning my studies, I would follow the advice of Plato and start with mathematics.
localization.Quote18Text: We see only what we know.
localization.Quote19Text: If anybody says he can think about quantum problems without getting giddy, that only shows he has not understood the first thing about them.
localization.Quote20Text: Only one thing is certain - that is, nothing is certain. If this statement is true, it is also false.
localization.Quote21Text: Scientists are explorers. Philosophers are tourists.
localization.Quote22Text: A great pleasure in life is doing what people say you cannot do.
localization.Quote23Text: Genius is one percent inspiration and ninety-nine percent perspiration.
localization.Quote24Text: I know one thing: that I know nothing.
localization.Quote25Text: Any sufficiently advanced technology is indistinguishable from magic.
localization.Quote26Text: When you want to know how things really work, study them when they're coming apart.
localization.Quote27Text: Engineers like to solve problems. If there are no problems handily available, they will create their own problems.
localization.Quote28Text: One man's "magic" is another man's engineering. "Supernatural" is a null word.
localization.Quote29Text: A good scientist is a person with original ideas. A good engineer is a person who makes a design that works with as few original ideas as possible. There are no prima donnas in engineering.
localization.Quote30Text: Aviation is the branch of engineering that is least forgiving of mistakes.
localization.Quote31Text: A space engineer is a professional practitioner who uses scientific knowledge, mathematics, physics, astronomy, propulsion technology, materials science, structural analysis, manufacturing and ingenuity to solve practical problems in space.
localization.Quote32Text: Space engineers design materials, structures, and systems while considering the limitations imposed by practicality, regulation, safety, ethicality and cost.
localization.Quote33Text: Space engineers are grounded in applied sciences, and their work in research and development is distinct from the basic research focus of space scientists.
localization.Quote34Text: In war times, space engineering involves military engineering as well. Such tasks typically include construction and demolition tasks under combat conditions.
localization.Quote35Text: Space engineers are in a high demand, especially since the Second Space Race of 2029.
localization.Quote36Text: Space engineers take pride for their ability to get the job done right - no matter how big, how complex, or how remote.
localization.Quote37Text: The word engineer is derived from the Latin roots 'ingeniare' ("to contrive, devise") and 'ingenium' ("cleverness").
localization.Quote38Text: To the optimist, the glass is half full. To the pessimist, the glass is half empty. To the engineer, the glass is twice as big as it needs to be.
localization.Quote39Text: Scientists investigate that which already is; engineers create that which has never been.
localization.Quote41Text: If you see a bomb technician running, follow him.
localization.Quote42Text: The only time you have too much fuel is when you're on fire.
localization.Quote44Text: A pilot who doesn't have any fear probably isn't flying his plane to its maximum.
localization.Quote45Text: To an engineer, good enough means perfect. With an artist, there's no such thing as perfect.
localization.Quote46Text: Mars is there, waiting to be reached.
localization.Quote47Text: This is one small step for a man, one giant leap for mankind.
localization.Quote48Text: I see Earth! It is so beautiful!
localization.Quote49Text: I could have gone on flying through space forever.
localization.Quote50Text: To go places and do things that have never been done before - that's what living is all about.
localization.Quote51Text: Do not go where the path may lead, go instead where there is no path and leave a trail.
localization.Quote52Text: To be the first to enter the cosmos, to engage, single-handed, in an unprecedented duel with nature - could one dream of anything more?
localization.Quote53Text: The path of a cosmonaut is not an easy, triumphant march to glory. You have to get to know the meaning not just of joy but also of grief, before being allowed in the spacecraft cabin.
localization.Quote54Text: The dreams of yesterday are the hopes of today and the reality of tomorrow.
localization.Quote56Text: No amount of experimentation can ever prove me right; a single experiment can prove me wrong.
localization.Quote57Text: Science never solves a problem without creating ten more.
localization.Quote58Text: The law of conservation of energy states that energy can be neither created nor destroyed. However, energy can change forms, and energy can flow from one place to another. The total energy of an isolated system remains the same.
localization.Quote59Text: The flow of heat is a form of energy transfer. In other words, a quantity of heat that flows from a hot body to a cold one can be expressed as an amount of energy being transferred from the hot body to the cold one.
localization.Quote60Text: Every body persists in its state of being at rest or of moving uniformly straight forward, except insofar as it is compelled to change its state by force impressed.
localization.Quote61Text: An object that is at rest will stay at rest unless an external force acts upon it.
localization.Quote62Text: An object that is in motion will not change its velocity unless an external force acts upon it.
localization.Quote63Text: The acceleration of a body is directly proportional to, and in the same direction as, the net force acting on the body, and inversely proportional to its mass.
localization.Quote64Text: To every action there is always an equal and opposite reaction: or the forces of two bodies on each other are always equal and are directed in opposite directions.
localization.Quote65Text: SCIENTIFIC METHOD: principles and procedures for the systematic pursuit of knowledge involving the recognition and formulation of a problem, the collection of data through observation and experiment, and the formulation and testing of hypotheses.
localization.Quote66Text: To be termed scientific, a method of inquiry must be based on empirical and measurable evidence subject to specific principles of reasoning.
localization.Quote67Text: The laws of science or scientific laws are statements that describe, predict, and perhaps explain why, a range of phenomena behave as they appear to in nature.
localization.Quote68Text: Scientific laws are strongly supported by empirical evidence - they are scientific knowledge that experiments have repeatedly verified (and never falsified).
localization.Quote69Text: Every point mass in the universe attracts every other point mass with a force that is directly proportional to the product of their masses and inversely proportional to the square of the distance between them.
localization.RemoteAccess_Description:
You can remotely access grids in the world using the antenna in your suit. Make sure your antenna is enabled.
(Check the antenna symbol in the bottom left corner of the in-game HUD)

To access a grid, it must be powered and have an antenna. You also need to stay within the antenna broadcast range to be able to access it.

You can control grids from a distance by equipping them with a remote control block.

localization.ToolTipWorldSettingsHarvestingMode:
Creative Mode: unlimited resources, instant building, players don't die. Use creative mode when you
just want to build things.

Survival Mode: realistic inventory capacity, constrained resources - you have to drill and harvest ore, process it
in a refinery, construct components in assembler, build blocks using welder, disassemble using grinder,
players can die - they re-spawn in their spawn point and if there's no spawn point available, then in a new ship
as a new player at the border of the sector.

Survival x3: same as "Survival", but 3x larger inventory capacity.

Survival x10: same as "Survival", but 10x larger inventory capacity.

localization.WelcomeScreen_Text1: I would first like to personally thank you for choosing to support our game and its development. Many talented people been involved in this project during the last six years and we are honoured to have you join our community.
localization.WelcomeScreen_Text2:
A space engineer is a professional practitioner who uses scientific knowledge, mathematics, physics, astronomy, propulsion technology, materials science, structural analysis, manufacturing, and ingenuity to solve practical problems in space and on planets.

Space engineers take pride in their ability to get the job done right. No matter how big, how complex, or how remote.
localization.WelcomeScreen_Text3:
If you experience any issues, please do not hesitate to visit the support site or our Discord server where there are developers and many experienced players available to assist you!

localization.IngameHelp_HUD_Detail1:
Cycle through the various HUD states; they differ by amount of shown information.
You can also change the way signals show up on your HUD.
localization.IngameHelp_HUD_Detail2: Press {CONTROL:TOGGLE_HUD} to cycle through HUD states.
localization.IngameHelp_HUD_Detail2:Gamepad: Press {CONTROL:SYSTEM_RADIAL_MENU} navigate to the [Quick Actions] tab and select the [Toggle HUD] option to cycle through HUD states.
localization.IngameHelp_HUD_Detail3: Press {CONTROL:TOGGLE_SIGNALS} to cycle through signal states.
localization.IngameHelp_HUD_Detail3:Gamepad: Press {CONTROL:SYSTEM_RADIAL_MENU} navigate to the [View] tab and select the [Signals] option to cycle through signal states.
localization.IngameHelp_Jetpack2_Detail1: Turning off dampeners while flying allows you to move without slowing down when you let go of the input. This can be useful to move steady at low or high speeds without using much fuel.
localization.IngameHelp_Jetpack2_Detail2:Gamepad: Swith between dampener modes with {CONTROL:DAMPING} while flying.
localization.IngameHelp_Building_Detail1: You can build blocks anywhere in the world or add them to existing grids. The toolbar config screen will show you all available blocks that you can build.
localization.IngameHelp_Building_Detail2: Press {CONTROL:BUILD_SCREEN} to open toolbar config screen.
localization.IngameHelp_Building_Detail3: Drag a block to your toolbar.
localization.IngameHelp_Building_Detail4: Select a block or tool by pressing 1 - 9
localization.IngameHelp_Building_Detail2_Gamepad: Press {CONTROL:TOOLBAR_RADIAL_MENU} to open the [Building Radial Menu].
localization.IngameHelp_Building_Detail4_Gamepad: Highlight a block with {GAMEPAD:AXIS_MOTION} and press {CONTROL:GUI:SHIFT_RIGHT} to select a block.
localization.IngameHelp_Building2_Detail1: Most blocks come in two sizes and can be rotated in any direction.
localization.IngameHelp_Building2_Detail2: Select the same block twice on your toolbar to pick a size.
localization.IngameHelp_Building2_Detail4_Gamepad: Use {CONTROL:BUILD:ROTATE_AXIS_LEFT} and {CONTROL:BUILD:ROTATE_AXIS_RIGHT} to rotate around the axis.
localization.IngameHelp_Building3_Detail1: In survival mode you need the first component of a block to place it. You can produce components in assembler or salvage them from other blocks with a grinder.
localization.IngameHelp_Ownership_Detail1: Blocks owned by other players cannot be accessed if they are not shared with others. You can hack blocks by replacing their computer parts  with a grinder and welder to gain access.
localization.IngameHelp_CameraTip_Detail1: You will be building in no time!
localization.IngameHelp_CameraTip_Detail2: *Tip:* Third person camera will switch to first person if there are objects in your way.
localization.IngameHelp_Power_Detail1:
Blocks or entire grids can be turned off to save power and fuel. 
When you are in a cockpit, Press {CONTROL:TOGGLE_REACTORS} to turn off and on the power production blocks.
localization.IngameHelp_BuildingTip_Detail2: *Tip:* Blocks with a + symbol have variations available that you can scroll through.
localization.IngameHelp_HUDTip_Detail1: I could not have done it better myself!
localization.IngameHelp_HUDTip_Detail2: *Tip:* HUD signals can be individually disabled in your terminal control panel.
localization.IngameHelp_HUDTip_Detail2:Gamepad:
*Tip:* HUD signals can be individually disabled in your terminal control panel.
In creative mode you can also cycle through signals using {CONTROL:TOGGLE_SIGNALS}.
localization.IngameHelp_IntroTip_Detail2: *Tip:* You can ask me anything in the chat {CONTROL:CHAT_SCREEN} using ? <question> (english only). In case of any troubles contact us at support@keenswh.com
localization.IngameHelp_IntroTip_Detail2:Gamepad:
*Tip:* You can ask me anything in the chat using ? <question> (english only). To open the chat window press {CONTROL:SYSTEM_RADIAL_MENU}, navigate to the [Menu] tab and select the [Chat] option.
In case of any troubles contact us at support@keenswh.com
localization.IngameHelp_JetpackTip_Detail1: That is my definition of flying!
localization.IngameHelp_JetpackTip_Detail2: *Tip:* Use relative dampening with [Ctrl+]{0} to keep velocity of the ship under cursor.
localization.IngameHelp_JetpackTip_Detail2:Gamepad: *Tip:* Use the relative dampening mode (auto) to match the velocity of the ship under the cursor.
localization.IngameHelp_InventoryTip_Detail2: *Tip:* You can drag items out of your inventory to drop them again.
localization.IngameHelp_Inventory_Detail1: Highlighted objects can be picked up if there is room in your inventory.
localization.IngameHelp_Inventory_Detail2: Press {CONTROL:USE} to pick up an item.
localization.IngameHelp_EnergyTip_Detail2: *Tip:*  Energy drains faster when it is hot or cold.
localization.IngameHelp_Energy_Detail1: Your energy is getting low. Interact with a powered medical bay or survival kit to recharge your energy or use any kind of cockpit. Your tools need energy to function.
localization.IngameHelp_HealthTip_Detail2: *Tip:* You will also slowly heal in oxygenated environments.
localization.IngameHelp_Health_Detail1: You're hurt. You can heal by interacting with the console of a powered medical bay or survival kit.
localization.IngameHelp_HydrogenTip_Detail1: I think you are smarter than my maker!
localization.IngameHelp_HydrogenTip_Detail2: *Tip:* You can conserve hydrogen when in space by flying with dampeners off.
localization.IngameHelp_Hydrogen_Detail1: Your hydrogen is getting low. Hydrogen is produced from ice in a O2/H2 generator. You can refill bottles at the generator or resupply directly by interacting with a medical bay or survival kit if it's connected with the O2/H2 generator.
localization.IngameHelp_MagneticBootsTip_Detail1: The last Engineer took much longer to figure this out!
localization.IngameHelp_MagneticBoots_Detail1: In zero gravity you can use your magnetic boots to walk on any surface. Position yourself with your feet down and turn off your jetpack to automatically lock your magnetic boots.
localization.IngameHelp_MagneticBoots_Detail2: Use your magnetic boots in zero gravity.
localization.IngameHelp_OxygenTip_Detail1: Breathing is preferable to not breathing!
localization.IngameHelp_OxygenTip_Detail2: *Tip:* Walking consumes less oxygen than running or sprinting
localization.IngameHelp_Oxygen_Detail1: Your oxygen is getting low. Oxygen is produced from ice in a O2/H2 generator. You can refill bottles at the generator or resupply directly by interacting with a medical bay or survival kit if it's connected with the O2/H2 generator.
localization.IngameHelp_FlyingAShipTip_Detail1: Pilots take no special joy in walking. Pilots like flying. - Neil Armstrong
localization.IngameHelp_FlyingAShipTip_Detail2: *Tip:* You need thrusters in all six directions. More thrusters means faster acceleration!
localization.IngameHelp_FlyingAShip_Detail1:
A ship requires thrusters for movement, gyroscopes to orientate,  power and a cockpit. 
The controls for a ship are the same as the jetpack.
localization.IngameHelp_FlyingAShip_Detail2: Press {CONTROL:TOGGLE_REACTORS} to toggle power on or off.
localization.IngameHelp_FlyingAShip_Detail3: Use {CONTROL:JUMP} and {CONTROL:CROUCH} to go up and down.
localization.IngameHelp_Grinder_Detail1: A  grinder is used to deconstruct and salvage blocks by removing their components into your inventory.
localization.IngameHelp_Grinder_Detail2: Hold {CONTROL:TOOLS:PRIMARY_TOOL_ACTION} to use grinder on any block.
localization.IngameHelp_GrinderTip_Detail1: You made quick work of that!
localization.IngameHelp_GrinderTip_Detail2: *Tip:* Grinder's can be used to remove trees.
localization.IngameHelp_HandDrill_Detail1: A hand drill is used to break down rock, collect minerals or to dig tunnels. Ores can be found in asteroids and dark spots on planets. All drills are equipped with a short-range detector.
localization.IngameHelp_Rifle_Detail1: A basic weapon to protect yourself; requires small calibre ammunition.
localization.IngameHelp_Rifle_Detail2: *Tip:* There are more specialized rifles available. Don’t forget that you can review useful information anytime in the help screen by pressing {CONTROL:HELP_SCREEN}.
localization.IngameHelp_Rifle_Detail2:Gamepad: *Tip:* There are more specialized rifles available. Don’t forget that you can review useful information anytime in the help screen by accessing the [Help] option in the [Menu] tab of the [System Radial Menu] {CONTROL:SYSTEM_RADIAL_MENU}.
localization.IngameHelp_WelderTip_Detail2: *Tip:* Use the {CONTROL:TOOLS:SECONDARY_TOOL_ACTION} to store components from your inventory into a block under construction.
localization.IngameHelp_Welder_Detail1: A  welder is used to construct and repair blocks by adding the required components from your inventory.
localization.IngameHelp_Welder_Detail2: Hold {CONTROL:TOOLS:PRIMARY_TOOL_ACTION} to use the welder on any block.
localization.IngameHelp_RefiningOre_Detail1:
Ore and scrap metal can be refined into ingots in a powered Refinery. 
Ingots can be used to produce components, tools and weapons.
Refineries will automatically pull resources and refine them.
localization.IngameHelp_RefiningOre_Detail2: Use a survival kit or Refinery to process ore and obtain ingots.
localization.IngameHelp_ComponentsTip_Detail1: Your skills are quickly becoming superior to mine!
localization.IngameHelp_ComponentsTip_Detail2: *Tip:* Blocks with a + symbol have variations available that you can scroll through.
localization.IngameHelp_Components_Detail1: Components are used to build and repair blocks. You can use a welder on any block to add the required component. You can select tools and blocks on your toolbar.
localization.IngameHelp_FlashlightTip_Detail1: A little light goes a long way!
localization.IngameHelp_FlashlightTip_Detail2: *Tip:* Remember, your flashlight consumes power from your suit.
localization.IngameHelp_Flashlight_Detail1: Use your flashlight when entering dark areas.
localization.IngameHelp_Flashlight_Detail2: Press {CONTROL:HEADLIGHTS} to toggle your flashlight off and on.
localization.IngameHelp_Ingots_Detail1: Ingots can be used by a survival kit or assembler to produce components, tools and weapons. You can select what component to produce in the assembler's or survival kit's menu.
localization.IngameHelp_Ingots_Detail2: Put iron ingot into Assembler inventory.
localization.IngameHelp_Ingots_Detail3: Use a survival kit or Assembler to produce and obtain steel plates.
localization.IngameHelp_InteractiveTip_Detail1: These skills will serve you well!
localization.IngameHelp_InteractiveTip_Detail2: *Tip:* Build control panels to easily access ship menus.
localization.IngameHelp_Interactive_Detail1: Many blocks like doors, button panels, consoles, medical rooms, inventories and cockpits support various different actions.
localization.IngameHelp_Interactive_Detail2: Press {CONTROL:USE} to activate a highlighted block.
localization.IngameHelp_Interactive_Detail3: Press {CONTROL:TERMINAL} to go to menu of highlighted block.
localization.IngameHelp_Interactive_Detail4: Press {CONTROL:INVENTORY} to open inventory of highlighted block.
localization.IngameHelp_PowerTip_Detail2: *Tip:* Turn off blocks that you do not need to save power.
localization.IngameHelp_PowerTip_Detail3: *Tip:* Use [Ctrl+]{CONTROL:TOGGLE_REACTORS} to also turn off all connected grids.
localization.IngameHelp_PowerTip_Detail3:Gamepad: *Tip:* Use {CONTROL:TOGGLE_REACTORS_ALL} to also turn off all connected grids.

localization.Description_FAQ_Electricity: Electricity can be produced through reactors or solar panels and stored in batteries. It is transferred automatically through all connected blocks. Many blocks require electricity to function.
localization.Description_FAQ_Asteroids: Asteroids can be found in space. How many there are depends on the server or world settings. Most asteroids will have ores that can be mined.
localization.Description_FAQ_Gravity: There is gravity on planets. Virtual Gravity can also be produced with the gravity generator block. Virtual gravity has no effect on grids unless virtual mass blocks are implemented.
localization.Description_FAQ_Oxygen: Some planets have breathable atmospheres. Oxygen can be produced from ice with a O2/H2 generator or from an oxygen farm. Oxygen can be stored in oxygen tanks and bottles.
localization.Description_FAQ_Damage: Damage can be inflicted by using weapons like rocket launchers or gatling turrets or hand held rifles. Grids can also be damaged by impacts with other grids or voxels.
localization.Description_FAQ_Repair: Use your welder to repair damaged blocks. Blocks that have been completely destroyed need to be replaced or you can use a projector to repair faster.
localization.Description_FAQ_Welding: Use your welder on blocks to build and repair. Welding requires power drawn from your suit and components for the block. You can also install welders on ships. Use RMB to add missing components from the block you are looking at to your build planner.
localization.Description_FAQ_Mining: You can collect ore by using your drill on voxels like planets or asteroids. Your drill has a short-range detector that shows you the location of ores.
localization.Description_FAQ_Healing: You can heal yourself at a medical room or survival kit if you are injured. Hold {CONTROL:USE} to use the console.
localization.Description_FAQ_Recharging: You can recharge your suit power in medical rooms, survival kits or by sitting in any kind of seat or cockpit as long as it is powered.
localization.Description_FAQ_Grinding: You can use a grinder to grind down blocks and deconstruct them. Components are salvaged and transferred into your inventory while grinding.
localization.Description_FAQ_Hydrogen: Hydrogen is a fuel used for your suit's jetpack and hydrogen thrusters. Hydrogen is produced from ice in a O2/H2 generator. You can story hydrogen in hydrogen tanks and bottles.
localization.Description_FAQ_Jetpack: Your jetpack requires hydrogen. You can produce hydrogen from ice in a O2/H2 generator. Refill bottles at the generator or connect the generator with a medical room or survival kit to recharge your hydrogen directly.
localization.Description_FAQ_MagneticBoots: Magnetic boots only work in zero gravity environments. They enable you to stick to surfaces like asteroids or ships. Press {CONTROL:THRUSTS} to disable your jetpack and enable your magnetic boots when in a standing position on a surface.
localization.Description_FAQ_Ore: Ore refers to several types of minerals that can be refined into ingots using a refinery. Ores can be found on planets and asteroids. Look for dark spots on planets to find ore.
localization.Description_FAQ_Ice: Ice is essential to produce oxygen and hydrogen and can be found on planets and inside asteroids.
localization.Description_FAQ_Voxel: Voxels are physical bodies such as asteroids or planets. Use your drill to bore into voxels and alter their shape. Use voxel hands in creative mode to create your own shapes.
localization.Description_FAQ_Grid: Grids are collections of blocks that shape stations or ships.
localization.Description_FAQ_Visor: Your visor can be opened and closed by pressing {CONTROL:HELMET}. Don't open your visor in space or you will suffocate!
localization.Description_FAQ_RoomPressure: Room pressure is displayed in a vent menu. A room has to be sealed in order to pressurized.
localization.Description_FAQ_Thrusters: Thrusters allow your ships to move and fly. Make sure to use the right thrusters in the appropriate environments. Atmospheric thrusters will not work in space!
localization.Description_FAQ_ShipMovement: Press {CONTROL:TOGGLE_REACTORS}  to turn power off and on. If you are wondering if you have enough power, check if there is fuel in your reactors or if your batteries are charged.
localization.Description_FAQ_RoverMovement: Press {CONTROL:LANDING_GEAR} to disable the brakes and landing gears or {CONTROL:TOGGLE_REACTORS} to turn the power off and on. You can check if there is fuel in your reactors or if your batteries are charged.
localization.Description_FAQ_Planets: Planets can be seen from any distance. If you do not see planets then they are likely not part of this world.
localization.Description_FAQ_Pirates: Protect yourself against pirates and other players by building armor, turrets and decoys.
localization.Description_FAQ_Fuel: Reactors use refined uranium ingots for fuel. Your jetpack and hydrogen thrusters require hydrogen.
localization.Description_FAQ_PCU: PCU stands for Performance Cost Unit.  Building and removing blocks cost and refunds PCU.
localization.Description_FAQ_Ownership: You can own blocks when you are the one who added the computer components. You can choose to share your blocks with your faction or anybody else.
localization.Description_FAQ_Factions: Factions are a way to play with other players by sharing your blocks, which can be used by other players. Anyone can set up factions.
localization.Description_FAQ_Bottles: Hydrogen and oxygen bottles can be produced in assemblers and refilled in O2/H2 generators.
localization.Description_FAQ_Help: Press {CONTROL:HELP_SCREEN} to find additional help or just ask me.
localization.Description_FAQ_SaveBlueprints: You can save ship designs in blueprints by aiming at them and press Ctrl-B. Press F10 to open your menu of blueprints.
localization.Description_FAQ_Lost: If you find yourself lost, you can always press {CONTROL:SUICIDE} to respawn at your nearest respawn point.
localization.Description_FAQ_Mass: Mass indicates the weight of your ship. Filling cargo containers with ores or components can severely impact the performance of your ship.
localization.Description_FAQ_Skins: Skins can be found in survival mode by finding the drop pods and activating their buttons. Use a medical room to customize your character.
localization.Description_FAQ_ShipInventories: Be sure to connect individual inventories using conveyors. Some items are too large to pass through small conveyor tubes. Press {CONTROL:INVENTORY} to open your personal inventory.
localization.Description_FAQ_ShipBuilding: The minimum requirements for a ship are a cockpit, gyroscope, one thruster in each direction and some form of power supply, such as a reactor or a battery.
localization.Description_FAQ_Script: Scripts might be disabled in world settings.
localization.Description_FAQ_GridMovement: Make sure it has thrusters pointing in the direction it is moving and some source of power.
localization.Description_FAQ_StopMoving: Be sure to enable your jetpack with {CONTROL:THRUSTS} and turn on your dampeners with {CONTROL:DAMPING}.
localization.Description_FAQ_RelativeDampeners: Relative dampeners match your speed and direction with a moving target. Press [Ctrl-{CONTROL:DAMPING}] while looking at your target. You need to be within 100 meters for it to work.
localization.Description_FAQ_InertiaDampeners: Inertia dampeners will slow movements when there is no input and can be toggled with {CONTROL:DAMPING}. Relative dampeners will match your speed with that of a moving object and can be toggled with [Ctrl-{CONTROL:DAMPING}]. Both need thrusters in all directions to work effectively
localization.Description_FAQ_Flashlight: You can toggle your flashlight with {CONTROL:HEADLIGHTS}. Flashlights consume suit power and will not work when depleted.
localization.Description_FAQ_FindOtherPlayers: Look for factions that allow anyone to join or ask around if you can group up with players. Look for antenna signals that could indicate other players.
localization.Description_FAQ_HowToPlayGame: Can you be more specific, please?
localization.Description_FAQ_Thing: Have you tried that other thing?
localization.Description_FAQ_ShipWontFly: Does your ship have enough power? Does it have enough thrusters? Are your dampeners turned on?
localization.Description_FAQ_WhatIsABlock: Blocks are what all ships and stations are made off. There are two sizes: large and small. You can find blocks in the menu by pressing {CONTROL:BUILD_SCREEN}.
localization.Description_FAQ_MirrorMode: Mirror mode only works in creative mode and allows symmetric building. Press {CONTROL:SYMMETRY_SWITCH} to cycle through all six planes of mirrors. Use LMB button to confirm placement and RMB to remove one. Press {CONTROL:USE_SYMMETRY} to temporarily disable mirror mode.
localization.Description_FAQ_ProtectingMyself: Hide your bases underground or inside asteroids. Build turrets and decoys to defend against attacks. Build hidden medical rooms and spread them out to maintain ways to respawn when attacked from inside you base.
localization.Description_FAQ_LosingHealth: Are you suffocating? Standing in front of a thruster or perhaps you came too close to an active ship tool?
localization.Description_FAQ_VoxelHands: Voxel hands is a tool only available in creative mode, which allows you to add and sculpt voxel shapes. It can be enabled in world settings. press K to open voxel hand menu while equiped.
localization.Description_FAQ_AirTightnessPressure: A room needs to be airtight before it can be filled with oxygen by an air vent. Make sure there are no holes exposed to space and that all doors are closed.
localization.Description_FAQ_Components: Components are required to construct blocks. They can be produced in assemblers from ingots. Placing a block in survival mode always requires the first component.
localization.Description_FAQ_Station: A station is a grid that is static and directly attached to voxels like planets or asteroids. Some stations can fly, but only have enough thrusters for basic movement.
localization.Description_FAQ_Ship: A ship is a grid that is designed to move. It has thrusters in each direction, a gyroscope for orientation, a cockpit and some source of power like batteries or reactors. Ships can be designed for specific tasks like building or fighting.
localization.Description_FAQ_CarRover: A rover is a vehicle that uses wheels to move instead of thrusters, which are used to fly. Rovers are usually cheap to build, but often slow and an easy target for other players.
localization.Description_FAQ_GPSSignals: GPS signals can be disabled or created in the Coms tab. Double-click a GPS signal to disable it. GPS signals can be stored in LCD panels or broadcasted in chat. Be careful not to attract enemies.
localization.Description_FAQ_GridSize: There are 2 grid sizes available that are simply referred to as small and large. You can switch the grid size of a block by reselecting the same block on your toolbar. Not all blocks are available in both grid sizes.
localization.Description_FAQ_Suit: Your suit keeps you alive when you are in space. Your health, hydrogen, oxygen and power supplies are displayed on your HUD. Your suit is equipped with magnetic boots to walk in space and a jetpack to fly.
localization.Description_FAQ_HandTools: There are 3 hand tools. A welder builds and repairs. A grinder salvages and deconstructs, while a drill is used to find ore, collect ore and dig tunnels.
localization.Description_FAQ_Inventory: Your inventory can be accessed by pressing {CONTROL:INVENTORY}. Drag items outside of your inventory screen to drop them. Pick up items by pressing {CONTROL:PICK_UP}.
localization.Description_FAQ_ShipToolsWeapons: Tools can be added to your toolbars by pressing {CONTROL:BUILD_SCREEN}. Drag and drop or right-click tools to automatically add them to your toolbar. This works the same for ship functions when you are inside a cockpit.
localization.Description_FAQ_Ingots: Ingots are produced in refineries from ores and are essential to produce components.
localization.Description_FAQ_Armor: Armor is used to design the structure of ships and stations, and acts as protection for important blocks. Light armor is cheap and enables ships to be fast. Heavy armor offers more protection for ships, but it affects these vehicles' speed.
localization.Description_FAQ_Meteor: Meteors can be enabled in world settings. You can protect yourself against meteors by building gatling turrets, adding layers of armor to vehicles and buildings or by simply hiding inside structures.
localization.Description_FAQ_UnknownSignals: Signals indicate positions of pods where you can obtain loot and skins in survival mode. Weak signals are only visible for you. Stronger signals are visible for everyone on the server but may lead to better loot.
localization.Description_FAQ_GPSColors: Blue Signals are owned by you. White signals are owned by a friendly faction. Red signals are owned by a hostile faction. Green and yellow signals indicate loot pods.
localization.Description_FAQ_Drones: Drones are small unmanned ships that can either be remote controlled, script controlled or sometimes controlled by sensors and timer blocks.
localization.Description_FAQ_Objective: Space Engineers is a sandbox game. You can set your own goals. Search the workshop for scenarios and missions or create your own to play together with friends! Active mission objectives are displayed in the top left corner.
localization.Description_FAQ_GoodBot: I am Good.bot. I am here to answer your questions to the best of my ability. How can I help you?
localization.Description_FAQ_Math: Math! I do that all the time!
localization.Description_FAQ_Begin: Get your production up and running. Build refineries and assemblers. Make sure you have enough power, Build solar panels, batteries and reactors. make sure your medical room is well protected and build more to be sure!
localization.Description_FAQ_BasicMovement: Use {CONTROL:FORWARD} {CONTROL:STRAFE_LEFT} {CONTROL:BACKWARD} {CONTROL:STRAFE_RIGHT} to move, Hold {CONTROL:SPRINT} to sprint, Toggle {CONTROL:SWITCH_WALK} to walk. Use {CONTROL:CROUCH} to crouch and {CONTROL:JUMP} to jump.
localization.Description_FAQ_Time: It is time for Space Engineers!
localization.Description_FAQ_SteamWorkshop: The {0} workshop is where you can find all player made blueprints, scenarios, scripts and mods that players published. Subscribe to workshop items to access them in game.
localization.Description_FAQ_Painting: While holding a block, you can paint blocks with {CONTROL:CUBE_COLOR_CHANGE}. Press K to access more colour options. Use Ctrl-{CONTROL:CUBE_COLOR_CHANGE} or Shift-{CONTROL:CUBE_COLOR_CHANGE} to paint large surfaces.
localization.Description_FAQ_InvalidMaterial: Sorry, That material does not exist in Space Engineers.
localization.Description_FAQ_Broadcasting: Your suit has a limited range antenna for accessing grids remotely or controlling drones. You can turn it off and on with O.
localization.Description_FAQ_BlockRotation: You can turn on the block and grid rotations assist in the game options menu to see the rotation controls. Press {CONTROL:CUBE_DEFAULT_MOUNTPOINT} to rotate a block towards its default mount-point.
localization.Description_FAQ_HUD: You can switch between HUD states with {CONTROL:TOGGLE_HUD}. Toggle {CONTROL:TOGGLE_SIGNALS} to switch between modes for GPS signals.
localization.Description_FAQ_Bug: You can report bugs and problems with the game at the forums or visit https://support.keenswh.com/
localization.Description_FAQ_Messages: You can send private messages to other players or factions through the Coms tab in your inventory. These messages can only be send if your antenna is enabled and in range of other players or antennas.
localization.Description_FAQ_AutoPilot: To use autopilot your ship first needs a Remote Control block. You need to add custom GPS waypoints in the Remote Control Block and select a flight mode. You can also set actions to happen when the ship arrives at the next waypoint.
localization.Description_FAQ_Experimental: Experimental mode is a setting that enables features that are considered unstable and can possibly cause performance issues. Experimental mode can be enabled in game settings.
localization.Description_FAQ_Marek: Marek Rosa is the Founder and CEO of Keen Software House and GoodAI.
localization.Description_FAQ_GoodAI: GoodAI was founded by CEO/CTO Marek Rosa in January 2014 and performs research on the development of artificial intelligence.
localization.Description_FAQ_DisableHints: To disable Good.bot hints, press Escape, go to Options, go to Game and disable "Show Good.bot hints".
localization.Description_FAQ_Permissions: In multiplayer you need special permissions from an admin to be able to spawn blueprints, edit scripts or teleport. In single player you can turn on space master or change the world mode to creative.
localization.Description_FAQ_LeavePlanet: To leave a planet with an atmosphere you need a ship capable of going into space. The best way is to equip your ship with hydrogen thrusters and hydrogen tanks.
localization.Description_FAQ_Groups: You can use block functions of multiple blocks simultaneously by using block groups. Use Ctrl or Shift to select the ship blocks you wish to put into a group; enter a name in "Block group" on the right side of the screen and press Enter to create the block group.
localization.Description_FAQ_MergeGrids: You can connect grids with each other with landing gears or connectors. You can merge two grids of the same size type together permanently by using merge blocks or even rotors.
localization.Description_FAQ_Camera: You can change your perspective with {CONTROL:CAMERA_MODE} from first person mode to third person mode. Note that third person camera can clip back to first person if objects are obstructing the view.
localization.Description_FAQ_Ammo: You can create ammunition for your weapons and turrets in the advanced assembler if you have the right materials available.
localization.Description_FAQ_Airlock: An airlock permits the player to move freely in and out while keeping the interior pressurized. The easiest way to achieve this is by building a set of parallel doors but can be made much more advanced with air vents, timer blocks, button panels or scripts.
localization.Description_FAQ_Pushing: Player characters can push small grids by walking or flying into them if these grids aren't too heavy. If you want to push or pull heavy objects you will have to build a ship or rover and grab the object with landing gear.
localization.Description_FAQ_Upgrade: You can assemble better tools in the assembler. You can also upgrade the refinery and assembler by adding upgrade modules to make them faster, more efficient or less power consuming.
localization.Description_FAQ_GameMode: There are two game modes: survival and creative. In creative mode you won't need any materials to build your ships. You can change this game mode by selecting your world in your saves menu and change the settings.
localization.Description_FAQ_ScreenShot: You can make screenshots by pressing F12 by default. Or if you have Nvidia Ansel you can press Alt-F to enter capture mode.
localization.Description_FAQ_Unlock: You can unlock new blocks by fully constructing other required blocks. You can see what blocks will unlock the next block by viewing them in the G screen.
localization.Description_FAQ_Temperature: Temperature affects your suit systems and will drain your power faster in extreme conditions. Without power your suit will no longer protect you against extreme conditions and you may start taking damage.
localization.Description_FAQ_SpawnShip: Your spawn ship will have everything you need to get started. A survival kit, power and a O2/H2 generator for oxygen and hydrogen. You can take nonesential parts of your ship to use for your new base and scrap it entirely once you no longer need it.
localization.Description_FAQ_MetalScrap: Metal scrap appears when blocks are violently destroyed and can be melted back into iron ingots by putting them into a refinery.
localization.Description_FAQ_LogOut: You can use a cryo room to store your character before leaving the server. This will prevent your character from dying after some time and losing your toolbar. Make sure the room is supplied with oxygen and power.
localization.Description_FAQ_Interaction: Interactive objects like doors, cockpits and button panels are highlighted yellow and can be entered or interacted with by pressing  {CONTROL:USE}.
localization.Description_FAQ_Navigation: You can create GPS signals to store important locations and waypoints. Use an antenna or beacon to broadcast positions of grids, but be careful, as others can also see these marked locations. Use /GPS to quickly save your current location.
localization.Description_FAQ_CopyPaste: You can copy, paste and delete blocks and grids only in creative mode by pressing Ctrl+C, Ctrl+V and Ctrl-X.
localization.Description_FAQ_Tools: A welder to construct blocks, a grinder to deconstruct blocks and a drill to find ore and dig tunnels. All tools can be produced in assemblers or survival kits from basic materials.
localization.Description_FAQ_Commands: Use /help to find all chat commands.
localization.Description_FAQ_Platinum: Platinum is a rare material only found in asteroids and moons. There is no platinum on planets.
localization.Description_FAQ_Uranium: Uranium is a rare material only found in asteroids and moons. There is no uranium on planets.
localization.Description_FAQ_Stone: Stone can be refined into small amounts of basic minerals like Iron, Silicon and Nickel in refineries or a survival kit.
localization.Description_FAQ_BlockShapes: You can access alternative block shapes if you have a block equipped on your toolbar with an + symbol. Use the scroll wheel to switch to different shapes.
localization.Description_FAQ_BuildMode: You can toggle different building modes by pressing B.
localization.Description_FAQ_CarJump: Your car can use its suspensions to jump to get out of tight spaces. Hold and release X to charge the jump of your car. The strength of the jump is based on your suspensions strength setting.
localization.Description_FAQ_ConvertGrid: You can convert grids from station to ship or ship into station in a grid's info screen if this is enabled in the world settings.
localization.Description_FAQ_FlipRover: You can flip your rover by adding pistons and pushing itself up or you can try adding heavy blocks like batteries to your grid, so that it will fall over by changing its center of mass.
localization.Description_FAQ_Tutorial: Play "Learning to Survive" to learn about the basics of Space Engineers. Pay attention to the tooltips for blocks to learn about their functions and I will do my best to help you along the way!
localization.Description_FAQ_Encounter: Random encounters are shipwrecks, derelict vessels and pirate stations that can be found in space. They often broadcast a MAYDAY signal. Careful, exploring these encounters can be dangerous.
localization.Description_FAQ_Blastdoors: Blast door blocks are armor blocks that won't bend and fit in between layers of blocks, so they can move freely by rotors or pistons. They are useful to create large moving doors and platforms.
localization.Description_FAQ_BlockLimit: Block limits sets a limit to how many of each type of block each player can build to ensure server performance. Block limits can be disabled in the world settings.
localization.Description_FAQ_Hacking: Hacking a block can be done by using a grinder to remove the computer components from a block and placing them back with a welder to gain access to the block.
localization.Description_FAQ_Ladder: You can use ladders to traverse vertical spaces. Ladders can be stacked vertically. Press {CONTROL:USE} to interact with a ladder. Hold {CONTROL:FORWARD} or {CONTROL:BACKWARD} to go up and down. Press {CONTROL:JUMP} to get off the ladder.
localization.Description_FAQ_Decoratives: Decorative blocks allow players to decorate the interiors of large grid ships. Blocks such as the desk and kitchen are modular and can be combined together to create many shapes.
localization.Description_FAQ_IndustrialCockpit: The industrial cockpit is a sturdy decorative cockpit for large and small grids that features a large field of vision. This cockpit is useful for rovers and ships that need to work close to surfaces or other grids without damaging them.
localization.Description_FAQ_ConsoleBlock: The console block is a decorative block with the ability to project large and small grids scaled down.
localization.Description_FAQ_Emotes: Emotes are character animations that can be equipped on your toolbar from the G-screen or played by opening chat and entering / followed by the name of the emote you wish to play. for example: /EmoteName
localization.Description_FAQ_BuildPlanner: The build planner helps you to quickly access the components required to build blocks. Use your welders RMB function to add a block to your component list. Use the withdraw button from any inventories to automatically collect the required components if available and accessible.
localization.Description_FAQ_StylePack: The Style Pack ads more player skins, armor skins and emotes for you to use in game.
localization.Description_FAQ_ArmorSkins: Armor skins are different textures and patterns for your ships and stations. They can be applied the same way you paint grids. Press P to open the paint screen.
localization.Description_FAQ_NPCShip: There are cargo ships that travel the world around you. Coming near them can be dangerous as they consider you a threat.
localization.Description_FAQ_CooperativeMode: Cooperative mode will let assemblers automatically take a portion of the queue of another assembler, making them work together.
localization.Description_FAQ_SpectatorMode: You can access Spectator mode by pressing F8 to move around your camera freely and F7 to remain in the spectator camera while controlling your character. Spectator mode requires permissions and has to enabled in worlds settings.

localization.ScreenDebugAdminMenu_ReplayTool_Tutorial: How to use the Replay Tool:
1. Add as many characters as you need, then position them how you want them and save the world.
2. Switch to the character you wish to control using F6.
3. Click 'Record + Replay', and move the character as you wish.
5. Reload the world, do not save!.
If you wish to clear the recorded data, press Delete Recordings to start over.
If you wish to observe the recorded data, press 'Replay' and watch as the game replays the data.
If you wish to store the recorded data, reload the world, then save the game. Then, it will carry over to other sessions.

How to use the Replay Tool:
1. Add as many characters as you need, then position them how you want them and save the world. 
2. Switch to the character you wish to control using F6.
3. Click 'Record + Replay', and move the character as you wish.
4. Press escape to stop recording.
5. Reload the world, do not save!.
6. Repeat from step 2.
If you wish to clear the recorded data, press Delete Recordings to start over.
If you wish to observe the recorded data, press 'Replay' and watch as the game replays the data.
If you wish to store the recorded data, reload the world, then save the game. Then, it will carry over to other sessions.

By accepting this contract you are bound to fulfill all conditions of this contract in timely manner.

localization.ContractScreen_Deliver_Description_0:
A priority package is to be delivered to a client of us and we are looking for the right person for the job.
You will pay a mandatory collateral upon accepting this contract.
Failing to complete the contract within the time limit will result our client being quite unpleased with our services and your collateral will be lost. 
We are sure you are up to the task.
localization.ContractScreen_Escort_Description_0:
One of our cargo ship operators reported potential threats and is unable to proceed. 
We are in need of a pilot with the right equipment to escort this cargo ship safely until the treat has subsided.
You will be paid appropriately. Are you up for the job?
localization.ContractScreen_Find_Description_0: A container got lost during transit and a client of ours is eager to see it returned. Go to it's last known location and find this container.
localization.ContractScreen_Hunt_Description_0:
With the absence of organized law enforcement the responsibility falls to individual factions to make sure that criminals do not go unpunished.
With that said, we have received reports of the location of one such culprit and we need you to make an example of them, so that others are not tempted down the same path. 
Find and take the target down. Use hand-held weapons or tools for the full reward. You will be kept up to date of the latest reported position of your target.
localization.ContractScreen_ObtainDeliver_Description:
A client of ours has requested some specific goods they wish delivered to this station for pickup.
Obtain the goods and then deliver them to us. We will ensure you are adequately rewarded.

localization.ContractScreen_Deliver_Description_1:
A partnered station has not been able to supply one of its customers due to a shortage.
They have requested that we will fill the gap and deliver the order as soon as possible.
Accepting this contract will require collateral and said collateral will be forfeit if you fail to complete the assignment in time.
localization.ContractScreen_Deliver_Description_2:
We are looking for skilled couriers capable of handling jobs within a tight schedule. 
We require a mandatory collateral upon accepting this contract. You will be reimbursed and rewarded upon completing the contract but failing to do so will forfeit the collateral. 
Time is key, are you up for it?
localization.ContractScreen_Escort_Description_1:
A nearby transport requested assistance after detecting hostile activity in it's vicinity. 
Go to the transport and make sure it gets through in one piece. 
Your feats will dictate your compensation.
localization.ContractScreen_Escort_Description_2:
It looks like one of our competitors decided to resort to less conventional ways to beat the competition. 
Report to our cargo ship and keep it safe. Let them know we mean business. 
You will be rewarded based on your performance.
localization.ContractScreen_Find_Description_1: Due to a navigational error a cargo capsule was misdelivered and we only know it's rough whereabouts. We need someone capable of finding it before someone else does. Are you up for it?
localization.ContractScreen_Find_Description_2: We need someone to pick up a discreet package whose exact position is unknown. Locate this package for us and there will be a reward for you.
localization.ContractScreen_Hunt_Description_1:
It seems like someone has made a bit of a name for themselves at the expense of others and in doing so made some of our clients quite unhappy. 
We just received reports detailing this person's last known position. We will happily compensate you if you can track them down and take them out. 
To ensure proper identification of your target we would prefer you take them down with either weapons or hand tools, if you prefer. You will be more highly rewarded for doing so.
We will make sure you are updated with the last known location of the target. Are you up to the job?
localization.ContractScreen_Hunt_Description_2:
Someone has been causing a lot of trouble lately and we need someone who isn't afraid to deal with it. 
We will relay the target's last known position to you. Go there, find the troublemaker, and take them out.
You will receive the full reward if the contract is completed by means of hand-held weaponry.

localization.Datapad_Station_GPS_Content_1:
A friend of mine who works on a remote station called in saying he has some contracts ready. 
They pay a good amount so if you are looking for a job then that's the place to go. Good luck!
localization.Datapad_Station_GPS_Content_2:
So you are looking for more jobs or trade? Sure we can sort you out. 
Take a look at this place. It is a bit remote but rumor goes that pilots find good opportunities here.
localization.Datapad_Station_GPS_Content_3:
Some conflict between two factions left a field of debris and salvager are plucking the fruits by selling their findings to a nearby station that now has their stocks overflowing. 
If you are looking for good deals or work then this is the place to go.
localization.Datapad_Station_GPS_Content_4: There is plenty of work available if you know where to look. You should investigate this place, I heard there is a shortage on couriers.
localization.Datapad_Station_GPS_Content_5:
Some Merchant keeps bragging about some really good deals at a station he has been visiting but would not spill the details. 
However, I happened to "stumble" on his navigation computer during my maintenance shift and this position kept popping up. Go see if there is any truth in what that merchant said.
localization.Datapad_Station_GPS_Content_6: I used to visit this place at a regular basis during my engineering days and they always had some good deals available. Go see if they are still at it.
localization.Datapad_Station_GPS_Content_7: A station lost some its client's due to some conflict of interest between factions and is now looking for new hires. Interested? This is where you should go.
localization.Datapad_Station_GPS_Content_8: Looking for Reliable contracts? Good trades? Or just making good money? You are in luck! Opportunity awaits at these coordinates!
